---
// InvestingSection.astro
---

<section class="investing-wash py-28 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Section label -->
    <p class="font-inter text-rk-muted text-xs tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4 font-medium">
      Capital Strategy
    </p>

    <!-- Heading -->
    <h2
      class="font-outfit text-rk-text mb-12 leading-tight"
      style="font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 700;"
    >
      What's Next:<br />
      <span style="color: #A78BFA;">Capital &amp; Crypto</span>
    </h2>

    <!-- Body paragraphs -->
    <div class="space-y-6 font-inter text-rk-muted leading-relaxed" style="font-size: 1.0625rem;">

      <p>
        Reality Knights has always had a crypto thread running through it. Devon ran <span class="text-rk-text font-medium">learncryptotips</span> —
        a blog dedicated to breaking down crypto for everyday people — as one of the ventures under the umbrella.
      </p>

      <p>
        Bitcoin, Ethereum, Solana, and a handful of asymmetric bets form the backbone of Reality Knights'
        capital strategy. We're building toward meaningful positions, one consistent move at a time.
      </p>

      <p>
        No fund. No pitch deck. Just conviction and a long time horizon.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- Decorative divider / asset row -->
    <div class="mt-14 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      {['BTC', 'ETH', 'SOL', '+ more'].map((ticker) => (
        <span
          class="font-inter font-medium text-xs tracking-widest uppercase px-4 py-2 rounded-full"
          style="background: rgba(124,58,237,0.12); color: #A78BFA; border: 1px solid rgba(124,58,237,0.25);"
        >
          {ticker}
        </span>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
